### 1. Data Controller

This website is operated by **$__L_en_ELISSAVET**.

Email: **[$SITE_EMAIL_CONTACT](mailto:SITE_EMAIL_CONTACT)**

The controller is responsible for the processing of your personal data under
the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).

### 2. Personal Data We Collect

We only collect personal data that you choose to provide when you contact us by
email. This may include:

* Your email address
* Your name
* Any information you include in your message

We do not collect personal data automatically through this website and we do
not use tracking, analytics, or advertising cookies.

### 3. Purpose of Processing

We process your personal data only to:

* Respond to your inquiries
* Communicate with you about your request

We do not use your data for marketing, profiling, or automated decision making.

### 4. Legal Basis for Processing

We process your personal data under the following GDPR legal bases:

* **Consent** under Article 6(1)(a) GDPR when you choose to contact us
* **Legitimate interest** under Article 6(1)(f) GDPR to reply to your inquiry
  and maintain correspondence

### 5. Data Retention

We keep your personal data only as long as necessary to respond to your inquiry
and for any related administrative or legal obligations.

Email correspondence is normally retained for up to **24 months**, unless a
longer retention period is required by law.

You may request deletion of your data at any time.

### 6. Data Sharing and Processors

We do not sell or rent your personal data.

Your data may be processed by the following service providers solely for the
technical operation of the website and email communication:

* **Fastmail Pty Ltd** as our email service provider for receiving and sending
  emails
* **Netlify Inc.** for website hosting and technical infrastructure

These providers act as data processors and process personal data only on our
instructions. Their processing is governed by their own GDPR compliant privacy
and security policies.

### 7. International Data Transfers

Some technical data may be processed outside the European Union by our service
providers. Where this occurs, it is protected by appropriate safeguards such as
Standard Contractual Clauses or equivalent GDPR approved mechanisms.

### 8. Data Security

We take appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your
personal data against loss, misuse, unauthorized access, and disclosure.

### 9. Your Rights

Under the GDPR, you have the right to:

* Access your personal data
* Correct inaccurate data
* Request deletion of your data
* Restrict or object to processing
* Request data portability
* Withdraw your consent at any time

To exercise your rights, contact us at **[$SITE_EMAIL_CONTACT](mailto:$SITE_EMAIL_CONTACT)**.

You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection
authority.

### 10. Cookies

This website does not use cookies, analytics, tracking scripts, or advertising
technologies.

### 11. Changes to This Policy

We may update this policy to reflect legal or operational changes. The latest
version will always be available on this page with the updated date.
"

